This paper is about natural language processing and text generation, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning models, which could fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) or machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions perplexity, which is a common evaluation metric in neural network models, suggesting it could also fall under neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) or software engineering (cs.SD) for model evaluation.
